name: Urbanview Hotel Gita Inn Bali
address: Jl. Trijata No.51, Dangin Puri Kangin, Kec. Denpasar Utara, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80223, Indonesia
review 1:
Simple budget place that is showing its age in common areas, but  can be excellent value if booked online. The rooms are well-sized, aircon works, the showers can be boiling hot!
The receptionist is very friendly and allows early check-in.
There is a well-stocked minimarket right under it.
Alas, standards of cleanliness have markedly dropped between my first and second stay (so this seems to be a hit or miss) - but then the rate has also dropped even lower.
review 2: nice design, there is a swimming pool, comfortable dining room but the service is really bad. Receptionists not always stand by, dirty, and moving rooms up to 3 times. Moved from the first room because the toilet was broken. moved from second room due to power failure. I really disappointed with the service.
review 3: The hotel is shabby, the managers speak very little English. The room was filthy, full of marks on the walls, marks on the bed, the toilet is broken... I strongly advise against it.
review 4: Good room, nice staff, good view, and very cheap. There's a shop open until 12pm at down stair. This hotel is located at the center of denpasar, and its near to go every where. There's a drop and pick up facility by the hotel and its cost very cheap. And the most amazing is there's a rooftop garden and you can do bbq here. I love that we can access the swimming pool for 24 hours ‚ù§
